<subSubSection id="C3146527FFE9E51A509882E161AFF7B5" pageId="40" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFE9E51A509882E16203F935" blockId="40.[189,795,1513,2049]" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFE9E51A509882E16227F9B5" bold="true" box="[189,300,1513,1537]" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Comment</emphasis>
: When describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFE9E51A522F82E26185F9B5" authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="2003" box="[522,654,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variolatus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFE9E51A522F82E26185F9B5" box="[522,654,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Z. variolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a unique male from “ 
<collectingCountry id="F319763CFFE9E51A51B5810162FAF995" box="[400,497,1545,1569]" name="Malaysia" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="49CAF84EFFE9E51A51D881016145F995" box="[509,590,1545,1569]" country="Malaysia" name="Pahang" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Pahang</collectingRegion>
, Jerau Water Falls” 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F4B5DFFE9E51A50988121624DF9F5" author="PACE, R." box="[189,326,1577,1601]" pageId="40" pageNumber="157" pagination="33 - 78" refId="ref58630" refString="PACE, R. 2003: Aleocharinae della Penisola di Malacca (Malaysia) (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino 20 (1): 33 - 78." type="journal article" year="2003">PACE (2003)</bibRefCitation>
compared this species with other 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFE9E51A52C581226203F9D5" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFE9E51A52C581226011F9F5" box="[736,794,1578,1601]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Zyras</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
of various subgenera, but not of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFE9E51A52B281426011F9D5" authority="sensu" authorityName="SenSU" box="[663,794,1610,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="186" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFE9E51A52B2814261DAF9D5" box="[663,721,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Zyras</emphasis>
sensu
</taxonomicName>
strictu.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136ACFFE9E51A5098818161AFF7B5" blockId="40.[189,795,1513,2049]" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">
A study of the above male revealed that it is highly similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D2FFFE9E51A50FE81A26254F975" authorityName="Borneo" baseAuthorityName="BERNHAUER" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[219,351,1706,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Zyras" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis id="B97AEABEFFE9E51A50FE81A26254F975" box="[219,351,1706,1729]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Z. montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) and distinguished from that species only by slightly smaller size, slightly more irregular punctation of the pronotum, slightly shorter elytra with less coarse and less dense punctation, and a smaller aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFE9E51A510F802162B6F8F5" box="[298,445,1833,1857]" captionStart="Figs 260–277" captionStartId="63.[151,191,1987,2009]" captionTargetBox="[157,1395,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-126@63.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 260–277: Zyras morulus (260–265), Z. variolatus (266–270), Z. montanus (271–275), and Z. preangeranus from Java (276–277): forebody (260); antenna (261); abdomen (262); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (263–264, 266–267, 271–272, 276–277); paramere (265, 268, 273); male tergite VIII (269, 274); male sternite VIII (270, 275). Scale bars: 260–262: 1.0 mm; 263–277: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5888380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5888380/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Figs 266–270</figureCitation>
); for illustrations of the paramere and the male tergite and sternite VIII see 
<figureCitation id="13352A29FFE9E51A52A28041601DF8D5" box="[647,790,1865,1889]" captionStart="Figs 260–277" captionStartId="63.[151,191,1987,2009]" captionTargetBox="[157,1395,232,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-126@63.[151,1398,232,1971]" captionText="Figs 260–277: Zyras morulus (260–265), Z. variolatus (266–270), Z. montanus (271–275), and Z. preangeranus from Java (276–277): forebody (260); antenna (261); abdomen (262); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view (263–264, 266–267, 271–272, 276–277); paramere (265, 268, 273); male tergite VIII (269, 274); male sternite VIII (270, 275). Scale bars: 260–262: 1.0 mm; 263–277: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5888380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5888380/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">Figs 268–270</figureCitation>
. The specimen differs from the original description by having only antennomere XI (not antennomeres X–XI) yellow. A study of more material, including the 
<typeStatus id="54B5880EFFE9E51A529380A1601DF875" box="[694,790,1961,1985]" pageId="40" pageNumber="157">holotype</typeStatus>
, is needed to clarify if the observed differences should be interpreted as intra- or interspecific variation.
</paragraph>
